Data Management¶

  • Each row contains information for both the winner and loser, making the dataframe a wide match-by-match dataframe.
  • The goal is to split each row into two rows
  • Each new row represents match data per player, with a win outcome column (1 = win, 0 = loss)
  • After converting the wide data into tall data, I will feature engineer and clear the data

#Some Feture Engineering
def split_tourney_date(data):
    data['tourney_year'] = data.tourney_date.astype(str).str[:4]
    data['tourney_month'] = data.tourney_date.astype(str).str[4:6]
    data['tourney_day'] = data.tourney_date.astype(str).str[6:8]
    data['tourney_date_str'] = data.tourney_date.astype(str).str[:8]
    data["tourney_date_str"] = pd.to_datetime(data['tourney_date_str'])
    data.drop(['tourney_date'], axis = 1, inplace = True)

#Get match summary information
def match_summary(matches):
    summaryColumns = ['tourney_name','tourney_year', 'name', 'ioc', 'rank', 'score','minutes', 'win_outcome']
    matchSummary = matches[summaryColumns]
    return matchSummary

def get_player_data(data, player):
    global tmpPlayerData
    tmpPlayerData = data[(data.name == player)]

#Logistic function
def run_logistic_regression(dataset, independent, dependent, testSize):
    """
    Parameters
    ----------
    
    dataset : DataFrame
        Data as pandas DataFrame
        
    indpendenet : list of str
        Predictor variable names that are in the provided dataset
        
    dependent : str
        Name of predicted Variable (1/0) in dataset
        
    testSize : float
        Proportion of dataset to designate as testing set
        
    seed : float
        Any number to set random_state
        
    
    """
    
    X = dataset[independent]
    Y = dataset[dependent]
    global xTrain, xTest, yTrain, yTest
    xTrain, xTest, yTrain, yTest = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size = testSize)
    
    global logReg
    logReg = LogisticRegression(solver = 'liblinear')
    logReg.fit(xTrain, yTrain)
    
    global logRegAccuracy
    logRegAccuracy = logReg.score(xTest, yTest)
    

    params = logReg.coef_
    global paramsDict
    paramsDict = dict(zip(independent,logReg.coef_[0]))
    paramsDict['intercept'] = logReg.intercept_
    

    from heapq import nlargest, nsmallest
    size = 5
    mostContribPos = nlargest(size, paramsDict, key = paramsDict.get)
    mostContribNeg = nsmallest(size, paramsDict, key = paramsDict.get)
    
    oddsRatio  = dict(zip(independent, np.exp(logReg.coef_[0])))
    oddsRatio


    print(f'Accuracy of Logistic Regression: {logRegAccuracy*100}')
    #print(paramsDict)
    #print('Variables that contribute the most (positively)\n', mostContribPos)
    #print('Variables that contribute the most (negatively)\n', mostContribNeg)
    print('\nVariables that contribute the most (positively)-- Odds Ratio')
    for predictor in mostContribPos: print(f'{predictor} : {np.exp(paramsDict.get(predictor))}')
    print('\nVariables that contribute the most (negatively)-- Odds Ratio')
    for predictor in mostContribNeg: print(f'{predictor} : {np.exp(paramsDict.get(predictor))}')

#Logistic with Cross Validation function
def run_logistic_regression_CV(dataset, independent, dependent, testSize):
    """
    Parameters
    ----------
    
    dataset : DataFrame
        Data as pandas DataFrame
        
    indpendenet : list of str
        Predictor variable names that are in the provided dataset
        
    dependent : str
        Name of predicted Variable (1/0) in dataset
        
    testSize : float
        Proportion of dataset to designate as testing set
        
    seed : float
        Any number to set random_state
        
    
    """    
    
    from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegressionCV
    
    global xCVTrain, xCVTest, yCVTrain, yCVTest
    xCV = dataset[independent]
    yCV = dataset[dependent]
    #Split for predictions 
    xCVTrain, xCVTest, yCVTrain, yCVTest = train_test_split(xCV, yCV, test_size = testSize)

    global logRegCV    
    logRegCV = LogisticRegressionCV(cv=10, solver = 'liblinear')
    logRegCV.fit(xCVTrain, yCVTrain)
    
    #Get Accuracy from the training sets only because LogisticRegressionCV automatically splits 
    #into training and testing each fold
    global aCV
    aCV =  logRegCV.score(xCVTrain, yCVTrain)
    
    #global logRegAccuracy
    #logRegAccuracy = logReg.score(xTest, yTest)
    
    
    #Predictions form Testing set
    global aCVPred
    aCVPred = logRegCV.predict(xCVTest)

    params = logRegCV.coef_
    global paramsDictCV
    paramsDictCV = dict(zip(independent,logRegCV.coef_[0]))
    paramsDictCV['intercept'] = logRegCV.intercept_
    

    from heapq import nlargest, nsmallest
    size = 5
    mostContribPos = nlargest(size, paramsDictCV, key = paramsDictCV.get)
    mostContribNeg = nsmallest(size, paramsDictCV, key = paramsDictCV.get)
    
    oddsRatio  = dict(zip(independent, np.exp(logRegCV.coef_[0])))
    oddsRatio


    print(f'Accuracy of Cross Validated Logistic Regression: {aCV*100}')
    #print(paramsDict)
    #print('Variables that contribute the most (positively)\n', mostContribPos)
    #print('Variables that contribute the most (negatively)\n', mostContribNeg)
    print('\nVariables that contribute the most (positively)-- Odds Ratio')
    for predictor in mostContribPos: print(f'{predictor} : {np.exp(paramsDictCV.get(predictor))}')
    print('\nVariables that contribute the most (negatively)-- Odds Ratio')
    for predictor in mostContribNeg: print(f'{predictor} : {np.exp(paramsDictCV.get(predictor))}')
